# ovh_vps_veeam_restore

Mounts (or fully restores) a Veeam restore point on a VPS. The resource
wraps the OVHcloud `POST /vps/{serviceName}/veeam/restorePoints/{id}/restore`
endpoint and waits for the underlying task to complete. Destroying the
resource calls `DELETE /vps/{serviceName}/veeam/restoredBackup` to unmount
the restore.

All attributes are `ForceNew` — the resource is immutable.

## Example Usage

```hcl
resource "ovh_vps_veeam_restore" "expose" {
  service_name     = "vps-xxxxxx.vps.ovh.net"
  restore_point_id = 12345
  full             = false
  export           = "nfs"
}

resource "ovh_vps_veeam_restore" "full_restore" {
  service_name     = "vps-xxxxxx.vps.ovh.net"
  restore_point_id = 12345
  full             = true
  export           = "smb"
  change_password  = true
}
```

## Argument Reference

* `service_name` - (Required, ForceNew) The internal name of your VPS.
* `restore_point_id` - (Required, ForceNew) ID of the Veeam restore point to mount.
* `full` - (Required, ForceNew) `true` to perform a full restore, `false` to only expose the backup over the chosen protocol.
* `export` - (Required, ForceNew) Export protocol used to expose the restore point. Must be `nfs` or `smb`.
* `change_password` - (Optional, ForceNew) Whether to change the VPS administration password. Only valid when `full = true`.

## Attributes Reference

* `state` - State of the restored backup.
* `access_nfs` - NFS access information.
* `access_smb` - SMB access information.
* `task_id` - ID of the restore task created on the OVHcloud side.

## Compatibility

This resource wraps `/vps/{serviceName}/veeam/restorePoints`. Live cross-region probing on 2026-05-26 shows
the endpoint is present in the **EU** and **CA** API schemas (`eu.api.ovh.com`,
`ca.api.ovh.com`) but **NOT** in the **US** schema (`api.us.ovhcloud.com`).

On a US-region VPS the OVHcloud API returns
`404: Got an invalid (or empty) URL`. Use this resource on EU or CA accounts,
or wait for OVH to expose this endpoint on US.
